Bob Pratt wrote:
> about a quarter turn in reverse. It still turns freely clockwise though. Any
> suggestions? I don't want to torque the case until I get the problem fixed.

Don't turn it backwards ;)

Try putting the distributor in so it holds the shaft down.  See if that 
fixes the problem.  Otherwise, try putting the shaft in after you mate 
the case halves.  I don't put it in until the very end because it's not 
that hard to get it oriented correctly.

Mike
